sentence: This is a great drawing app . I thought it was just going to be one of those stupid little doodle apps that serves no purpose but you guys proved me wrong . The only thing I would improve is that you could select and move the image around . Other than that , it is SUCH a perfect drawing app . 100 % would recommend . UwU -DragonTales

The only app I 've actually sought actively to positively review . I forgot to forever because it never bugged me for one . So I use a lot of art software on my phone , a ridiculous amount , but this is still my standby and tbh fave . It 's dead fast , it works , no ads or pestering , it 's a lovely little app . It barely leaves a footprint too , it 's bloody tiny . Ca n't hype it enough . Just a wonderful little utility .

The best simple paint\drawing app I 've found . It 's possible to do some quite complex picture editing with a good range of tools , much more than most simple draw apps offer . Minimal permissions , most importantly no Internet permission and no ads . It would be great to have options when saving . Unfortunately it reduces the resolution and removes the EXIF data ( most similar apps do the same ) , else it would be perfect .

So nearly a great app . But saving works badly ( you are n't prompted to choose a path ) , and the function i most need ( pixel perfect crop ) is impossible to use . It zones out every time you select it ... and it 's impossibly touchy and keeps committing before you 've finished adjusting . I tried about 15 times or more before giving up . Real shame as this is almost , otherwise what all the other apps fall to be . ( Simple and powerful )
Surprisingly good ! Good job devs , as long as it does n't end up drowning me in ads or locking out features as it grows , it certainly deserves 5/5 !

Do n't know what has happened . I 've used this app for several years , and loved it for it 's simplicity , ease of use , user friendliness , and wide range of capabilities . For some reason however , I 'm now having problems with it . Whenever I use the `` Fill '' function to put a transparent background in any sort of project I 'm working on , it now force-closes on me . As I said , I do n't know why it 's happening now , because I 've performed the exact same process countless times . Whenever you touch it the wrong way it 's either reapplying the clone or stamping the wrong thing everywhere ( leading to those dreaded undos ) . Still 2 stars though , because I did end up finishing it the way I wanted and there are literally no other halfway decent photo manipulators on here

It 's a good editor and has the potential to be even much , much more ! It can create pictures with transparency and is integrated with `` Pocket Code '' so it 's easy to take a created pick , drop it into Pocket code , then pull it back out and modify it , then re-save and repeat until it 's perfect . It still needs features like mirror , more shapes like polygons n-point , but it 's a very good start and pretty easy to use too ! Now it is a little laggy on undoes even on my Samsung Galaxy 5 , but with such a dedicated team as Catrobat I 'm sure it will really grow in to a truly amazing and professional editor/creator !
I draw cartoons easily on this app and can fill in the colors quickly with the `` paint bucket . '' There is no excuse for most drawing apps not to include this , but they do n't .
